The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 October is 77,617 (8,945.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 September, there were 2,521 new confirmed cases (290.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 September, there were 1,912 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 32% (609 extra cases).
